        "text": "The watch server enables you to edit code from your own text editor and have it injected and run inside the Croquet Microverse while it is running without the need to reload. The watch server is automatically launched when execute npm start. You can start the watch server on its own by running npm run watch-server. The watch-server by default starts watching the directory called behaviors/croquet for system behaviors and a directory specified in the world file, typically behaviors/default or another sub directory under behaviors.\n\nYou can try out the live text editor integration with the default world at http://localhost:9684. You will see a menu icon in the top right corner. Select this and you will see a large QR code and a few other menu items."
